{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1551124613,"nonce":"Zp3f2Lt8oQSz03N6xiUL7ghUrOQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0MTQyNzk0OTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2313","origin":"github"},"title":"MACS2 Fails with SAM input now -- intentional? Solutions to mitigate user confusion?","message":"Tool versions tested/history: \n* EU \u003e\u003e MACS2 callpeak Call peaks from alignment results (Galaxy Version 2.1.1.20160309.5) https://usegalaxy.eu:/u/jenj/h/test-macs2-bam-sam\n* ORG \u003e\u003e MACS2 callpeak Call peaks from alignment results (Galaxy Version 2.1.1.20160309.4) https://usegalaxy.org:/u/jen/h/test-history-bowtie2-macs2-diffbind\n\nMTS: https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=e984c9f63184b207\n\nProblems: \n* The tool used to accept/work with SAM input. \n* Appears that the tool form was modified to explicitly state that BAM/BED/BAMPE is expected. \n* Most tools that accept BAM also accept SAM. \n* SAM datasets show up in the tool's select menu.\n* User is not warning that SAM is not accepted -- on the tool form on in the GUI (most do not know how to review STDERR or what would be the actionable solution if they do find/review it). \n* **So ... it looks like a tool bug, even if intentional.**\n* **Of note:** The \"failed job\" with SAM input that will always fail again automatically resubmittes at EU. Not sure how many times it will cycle, but is a waste of resource + confusing for users.\n\nCan we think of some way to mitigate the issue? \n* Change the select to filter out SAM data? \n* Don't allow the job to submit if the input is not one of the three supported types (red select highlight with a warning like: \"Input is not in BED, BAM, or BAMPE format\"). \n* If those are not possible, at least the tool help should be modified -- with us knowing that \"more help\" text is nice but doesn't really help to _prevent_ usage problems like this. Nor auto-reruns.\n\nMessage in the red error dataset:\nEU \n```\nINFO  @ Mon, 25 Feb 2019 20:31:01: \n# Command line: callpeak -t /data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457806.dat --name BAM-to-SAM_on_data_3__converted_SAM -c /data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457807.dat --format BAM --gsize 2700000000\n```\n\nORG \n```\n/cvmfs/main.galaxyproject.org/deps/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-9745eaf08708c75d5cb939b005b2fbbcc13ccefcb86602af9e1bf012d47be274/lib/python2.7/site-packages/MACS2/OptValidator.py:27: RuntimeWarning: numpy.dtype size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility\n```\n\nError when bug report is click on: EU + ORG\n```\nFatal error: Exit code 1 ()\n```\n\nError in job info/stderr: EU capture, but same basic content at ORG\n```\nINFO  @ Mon, 25 Feb 2019 20:31:01: \n# Command line: callpeak -t /data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457806.dat --name BAM-to-SAM_on_data_3__converted_SAM -c /data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457807.dat --format BAM --gsize 2700000000 --keep-dup 1 --bdg --qvalue 0.05 --mfold 5 50 --bw 300\n# ARGUMENTS LIST:\n# name = BAM-to-SAM_on_data_3__converted_SAM\n# format = BAM\n# ChIP-seq file = ['/data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457806.dat']\n# control file = ['/data/dnb02/galaxy_db/files/008/457/dataset_8457807.dat']\n# effective genome size = 2.70e+09\n# band width = 300\n# model fold = [5, 50]\n# qvalue cutoff = 5.00e-02\n# Larger dataset will be scaled towards smaller dataset.\n# Range for calculating regional lambda is: 1000 bps and 10000 bps\n# Broad region calling is off\n# Paired-End mode is off\n \nINFO  @ Mon, 25 Feb 2019 20:31:01: #1 read tag files... \nINFO  @ Mon, 25 Feb 2019 20:31:01: #1 read treatment tags... \nException struct.error: 'unpack requires a string argument of length 4' in 'MACS2.IO.Parser.BAMParser.tsize' ignored\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/usr/local/tools/_conda/envs/mulled-v1-9745eaf08708c75d5cb939b005b2fbbcc13ccefcb86602af9e1bf012d4